Example scripts and data for a "double" fit to HI emission
and absorption pairs via GaussPy
(1) decompose_double.py : Decomposes input spectra, which must include both
absorption and emission profiles (absorption: x_values, data_list;
emission: x_values_em, data_list_em). To instruct GaussPy to perform
a "double" fit, the parameter "alpha_em" must be set (alpha_em = None 
means GaussPy will perform a standard fit). 
(2) plot_double.py : Plot the results of the "double" decomposition.
(3) example_data.py : Set of 4 example HI pairs from The Millennium Arecibo 
21 cm Absorption Line Survey (Heiles & Troland 2003a). 
